<subSubSection pageId="105" pageNumber="106" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1437,151,2038]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[525,726,939,965]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Aurora Rockfish</emphasis>
. To 
<quantity box="[775,844,939,965]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" unit="cm" value="41.0">41 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[860,919,939,966]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.064" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" unit="in" value="16.0">16 in</quantity>
) TL (
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer and O'Connell" box="[981,1308,939,966]" firstAuthor="Kramer" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" refId="ref292651" refString="Kramer, D. E. &amp; O'Connell, V. M. (1995) Guide to northeast Pacific rockfishes genera Sebastes and Sebastolobus. University of Alaska Sea Grant, Fairbanks, Marine Advisory Bulletin, No. 25." type="book" year="1995">Kramer and O’Connell 1995</bibRefCitation>
). Southeast 
<collectingRegion box="[198,276,975,1001]" country="United States of America" name="Alaska" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Alaska</collectingRegion>
(about 
<geoCoordinate box="[363,462,974,1001]" degrees="55" direction="north" minutes="56" orientation="latitude" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" precision="925" value="55.933334">55°56’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[474,592,974,1001]" degrees="135" direction="west" minutes="26" orientation="longitude" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" precision="925" value="-135.43333">135°26’W</geoCoordinate>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Laman and Orr" box="[616,855,975,1001]" firstAuthor="Laman" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="230 - 232" refId="ref293660" refString="Laman, E. A. &amp; Orr, J. W. (2011) First record of an aurora rockfish, Sebastes aurora, from Alaskan waters. Northwestern Naturalist, 92, 230 - 232. https: // doi. org / 10.1898 / 1051 - 1733 - 92.3.230" type="journal article" year="2011">Laman and Orr 2011</bibRefCitation>
) to Isla de Cedros, central Baja 
<collectingRegion box="[1220,1334,975,1001]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">California</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer and O'Connell" firstAuthor="Kramer" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" refId="ref292651" refString="Kramer, D. E. &amp; O'Connell, V. M. (1995) Guide to northeast Pacific rockfishes genera Sebastes and Sebastolobus. University of Alaska Sea Grant, Fairbanks, Marine Advisory Bulletin, No. 25." type="book" year="1995">Kramer and O’Connell 1995</bibRefCitation>
). Larvae have been taken off Banco Thetis (
<geoCoordinate box="[914,1014,1011,1037]" degrees="24" direction="north" minutes="40" orientation="latitude" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" precision="925" value="24.666666">24°40’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[1025,1144,1011,1037]" degrees="112" direction="west" minutes="18" orientation="longitude" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" precision="925" value="-112.3">112°18’W</geoCoordinate>
), southern Baja 
<collectingRegion box="[1323,1437,1010,1036]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">California</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Moser" box="[205,411,1046,1073]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Moser" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="55 - 64" refId="ref304087" refString="Moser, H. G., Sandknop, E. M. &amp; Ambrose, D. A. (1985) Larvae and juveniles of aurora rockfish, Sebastes aurora, from off California and Baja California. In: Kendall Jr, A. W. &amp; Marliave, J. B. (Eds.), Descriptions of Early Life History Stages of Selected Fishes. Third International Symposium on the Early Life History of Fishes. Canadian Technical Report Fisheries and Aquatic Sciences, 1359, pp. 55 - 64." type="journal article" year="1985">
Moser 
<emphasis box="[287,344,1046,1072]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">et al.</emphasis>
1985
</bibRefCitation>
), strongly implying that this species lives considerably farther south than its southernmost adult record. While Nelson 
<emphasis box="[519,579,1082,1108]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">et al.</emphasis>
(2004) notes that records of this species from off Baja 
<collectingRegion box="[1228,1342,1082,1108]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">California</collectingRegion>
may be based on errors in field identification, the presence of 
<taxonomicName box="[795,974,1118,1144]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Sebastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aurora">
<emphasis box="[795,974,1118,1144]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Sebastes aurora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larvae many hundreds of miles below the 
<collectingCountry box="[198,240,1153,1179]" name="United States of America" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">U.S.</collectingCountry>
– 
<collectingCountry box="[255,347,1153,1179]" name="Mexico" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Mexico</collectingCountry>
border strongly suggests the presence of adult fish in Mexican waters. If the species is not found in Mexican waters, the southernmost range is San Diego, southern California (
<bibRefCitation author="Phillips" box="[1087,1243,1189,1216]" firstAuthor="Phillips" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" refId="ref312016" refString="Phillips, J. B. (1957) A review of the rockfishes of California. California Department of Fish and Game Fish Bulletin, 104." type="book" year="1957">Phillips 1957</bibRefCitation>
). Benthic; depth: 
<quantity box="[198,332,1225,1251]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.285" metricValueMax="11.76" metricValueMin="0.8099999999999999" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" unit="m" value="628.5" valueMax="1176.0" valueMin="81.0">81–1,176 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[346,493,1225,1252]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.283452" metricValueMax="11.756136" metricValueMin="0.810768" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" unit="ft" value="2061.5" valueMax="3857.0" valueMin="266.0">266–3,857 ft</quantity>
) (min.: 
<bibRefCitation author="Wilkins" box="[582,798,1225,1251]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Wilkins" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" refId="ref333638" refString="Wilkins, M. E., Zimmermann, M. &amp; Weinberg, K. L. (1998) The 1995 Pacific West Coast bottom trawl survey of groundfish resources: Estimates of distribution, abundance, and length and age composition. NOAA Technical Memorandum, NMFS - AFSC - 89." type="book" year="1998">
Wilkins 
<emphasis box="[676,732,1225,1251]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">et al.</emphasis>
1998
</bibRefCitation>
; max.: NWFSC-FRAM).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
